Legal Pages for lisacolliorealtor.com

**APPROVED — July 2026 · Signed off as written by Lisa Collio and her Managing Broker (RE/MAX Results)**

Prepared under the Lisa Collio Website Master Plan (Section 18) and approved as written, July 2026. Contains the approval record and the four final page texts: Terms of Use, Privacy Policy, Accessibility Statement, and Fair Housing Statement. The analytics question has been resolved: the Site uses Netlify's server-side analytics only — no client-side tracking, no cookies placed. The one remaining bracket is each page's effective date, which Claude Code inserts on the day the page goes live. This document is a working reference, not legal advice.

# Approval Record

- **Status:** Approved as written — Lisa Collio and her Managing Broker (RE/MAX Results), July 2026. This satisfies the Master Plan Section 13 review gate for these four pages.

- **Decisions confirmed in this approval:** communications language describes actual practice (personal calls/texts from (574) 370-5410, no automated dialing); no lender or settlement-provider data sharing; California-specific statutory sections replaced by the plain-language consumer-rights section; English-only legal pages at launch, with Spanish courtesy versions to be revisited later with professional legal translation.

- **Resolved after broker review:** site analytics confirmed as Netlify server-side analytics — traffic measured on the server, no cookies placed, no individual tracking. The Privacy Policy's automatic-collection and cookies sections below reflect this.

- **Standing obligations:** if automated texting is ever enabled in GoHighLevel, the communications section must be updated to name the sending number and method BEFORE the feature goes live. If a lender referral relationship ever becomes active, a written Affiliated Business Arrangement disclosure must exist before any referral, and the Privacy Policy updates to match.

- **Publication:** these pages go live before or together with /contact/ — no lead-capture form launches without them. Claude Code inserts each page’s effective date at publication and applies the standard footer stack.

